main event: Possible satellite observed crossing the track of ECHO I in December 1964.
interesting points: ECHO I was not visible in the southern hemisphere., ECHO II was reported crossing the track of ECHO I., The satellite passed through a 70-degree arc heading southeast in 14 minutes., The observer was located at coordinates 29/1600 169-30W., The object was observed at an elevation of 49 degrees above the horizon.
